> > 
> > > I'm thinking about rebuilding the calipers on my 71 bus, but the 
> > Bentley manual makes it seem fairly complicated.  Is this something 
> > that can be easily done without all the special tools, or am I 
better 
> > off just purchasing remanufactured ones?  I have decent mechanical 
> > skills, if that makes a difference.
> > 
> > I've done it and it isn't particularly difficult.  _Don't_ separate 
> the 
> > caliper halves from each other!  You don't have to do this to 
rebuild 
> > and if you leave the seals undisturbed you won't have to replace 
them.
> > 
> > I used a small pair of vise-grips "backwards" to grip the piston 
from 
> > the inside.  I made a tool from PVC pipe to use with a C-clamp to 
> seat 
> > the dust seals.  Other than the dust seals being a bit hard to 
seat, 
> it 
> > was not difficult.  Be sure to replace the brake hoses at the same 
> time!
> > 
> > After you get the pistons out, inspect the cylinders.  If you find 
> > corrosion pitting, it's time for new calipers, so don't waste your 
> > effort in putting in new seals just to have them leak.
> > 
> > George Lyle
